  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6757 trading above the GEX flip at 6718, dealers are in negative gamma territory and forced to chase momentum - they're buying this rally which amplifies the move higher. The massive negative gamma wall at 6750 (-12.8B) acts as a launching pad below current levels, while the positive gamma ceiling at 6775 (+8B) will trigger dealer selling pressure if reached. Watch for potential rejection at 6775 as dealers flip to selling mode, but any break below 6750 could trigger accelerated selling as dealers hedge short gamma positions.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile trending moves with dealers amplifying any directional momentum until hitting the 6775 resistance zone.",
